title: CPaaS SDK for business communication solutions | Rainbow
metaDescription: Add chat, conference, real time collaboration and communication (PBX, VoIP, P2P) capabilities, bots and more to your business applications.
mainHtml:
Documentation

Changelog

LTS release 3.XPubli√©e le 2025-03-17

SDK (Core) for C#

[3.7.0] - 2026-01-16

Added

  • Administration service:
    • SetExternalPresenceAsync(), GetExternalPresenceAsync() and RemoveExternalPresenceAsync() methods to manage "external presence"
  • Application service:
    • Add optional parameter logoutUrl in LoginWithTokenAsync(), LoginWithTokenWithoutEventPipeAsync(), LoginWithTokenAsync() and LoginWithTokenWithoutEventPipeAsync() methods
    • UserCredentials object: add LogoutUrl and ApplicationToken properties
  • Bubbles service:
    • AutoClearBubbleContentAsync(), ClearBubbleContentAsync() methods
    • ConferenceDetails object: ContentToAutoClear property
    • BubbleAffiliation object: Reason property - possible values: "deactivated", "resumed" or empty
  • Contacts service:
    • CustomStatusUpdated event, CreateCustomStatus(), UpdateCustomStatusAsync(), DeleteCustomStatusAsync() and GetCustomStatusesAsync() methods to manage custom statuses
  • FileStorage service:
    • AddViewerAsync(), RemoveViewerAsync() and GetFileDescriptorSync() methods
  • InstantMessaging service:
    • ForwardMessageAsync() method: add optional parameter anonymously (True by default)
    • Message object: add ForwardedFromContact property
  • Peer object:
    • IsChannel(), IsChannelWithId(), IsChannelWithJid(), IsChannelWithIdAndJid(), static methods
    • IsEntity(), IsEntityWithId(), IsEntityWithJid(), IsEntityWithIdAndJid(), static methods

Fixed

  • Application service:
    • if used, ensure to check Turn Servers configuration based on theirs TTL
  • Bubble service:
    • join automatically a bubble which is no more inactive
    • avoid to trigger several times same BubbbleAffiliationChanged event
  • Conferences service:
    • Before to start a conference, ensure to set as active the associated bubble if necessary
  • Contacts service:
    • about presence correctly manage away versus away inactive states
  • FileStorage service:
    • avoid to trigger several times same FileStorageUpdated event
  • InstantMessaging service:
    • Store message in cache only if StorageMode is set to Store
    • Avoid to store message sent with <CDATA> section
    • Mark automatically message as read (if specified) only if StorageMode is Store or NoPermanentStore
    • When forwarding a message with a file, ensure to set the receiver as viewer of this file
    • Before to send a message to a bubble, ensure to set it as active if necessary

Removed

  • ConferenceDetails object:
    • Breaking Scheduled, ScheduledStartDate , ScheduledEndDate , ScheduledDuration , MediaType , LastUpdateDate, Sessions properties
  • Breaking ConferenceSession object::

[3.6.0] - 2025-11-20

Info

  • New RPC service (Remote Procedure Call)
    • As client permits to request RPC method of a Peer and get the result
    • As server permits to add / remove new RPC method: possibility to restrict access according RPC method and / or Peer
    • It's possible to be client and server in same time
    • Interaction between CPaaS Rainbow client (Web Client, Desktop Client) and SDK
      • CPaaS client offers default RPC Methods (make call for example) which can be requested from SDK
      • CPaaS client can request SDK RPC Methods using custom manifest file
  • Guest updates:
    • Can no more be created using CreateGuestUserAsync() and CreateAnonymousGuestUserAsync() in Administration service
    • Contacts with GuestMode still exist which are created using Bubble Link: see CreateUserWithBubbleLinkAsync() in Administration service

Fixed

  • Jingle service:
    • add more tests when sendinq Iq (to avoid use of null value for jid or resource)

Added

  • Added .Net 10.0 as target framework
  • Alerts service:
    • RemoveDevicesTagsAsync(), RenameDevicesTagsAsync() and GetDevicesTagsStatisticsAsync() methods
    • AlertFilter object with new field IpAddresses
    • AlertDevicesTagCount, AlertDevicesTagsStatistics, AlertFilterIpAddresses and AlertFilterIpAddresseRange objects
  • Contacts service:
    • IsCompanyAdminAsync() and IsCompanyAdminSync() methods
  • FileStorage service:
    • CreateArchiveAsync() method
    • QuotaConsumption object: add Recordings and Others properties
  • InstantMessaging service:
    • PrivateMessageReceived event
    • SendPrivateMessageAsync(), AnswerToPrivateMessageAsync() methods
    • Message object with new field PrivateMessage
  • JSONNode object:
    • Escape() method
  • Peer object:
    • IsContactWithIdAndJid(), IsBubbleWithIdAndJid() methods
  • Restrictions object:
    • UseRPC property (false by default)
  • RPC service:
    • CallMethodAsync(), ListMethodsAsync(), GetMethodHelpAsync(), GetMethodSignaturesAsync(), RestRequestAsync() methods (for RPC client)
    • AddMethod(), RemoveMethod(), DefineDelegateToAllowRPCRequests(), AllowAllRPCRequests() methods and AllowRestRequestAsRpcMethod property (for RPC server)
    • Base64, RPCRestRequest, RPCRestResponse objects
  • SdkInternalErrorEnum enum:
    • XMPP_IQ_ERROR, XMPP_IQ_TIMEOUT: to provide more error details in IQ context
    • RPC_PARSING_ERROR_METHODCALL_NODE, RPC_PARSING_ERROR_VALUE_NODE_TO_OBJECT, RPC_PARSING_ERROR_OBJECT_TO_VALUE_NODE, RPC_NO_METHOD_FOUND, RPC_NO_METHOD_FOUND_WITH_CORRECT_SIGNATURE, RPC_EXCEPTION_IN_METHOD, RPC_PARSING_METHOD_RESULT, RPC_UNEXPECTED_ERROR, RPC_NOT_ALLOWED
  • Util object:
    • XmlEncode() and XmlDecode() methods

Changed

  • Conferences service:
    • GetMediaPublications() method: if at least one Video MediaPublication is available, add to the list a MediaPublication useable as DynamicFeed.
  • FileStorage service:
    • GetAllFileDescriptors() method: add new optional parameter withRecordFiles (false by default)
    • GetAllFileDescriptorsReceived(), GetAllFileDescriptors(), GetFileDescriptorsAsync(), GetFileDescriptorsReceived(), GetFileDescriptorsReceivedAsync() methods: add new optional parameter recordingFiles (false by default)

Removed

  • Administration service:
    • Breaking CreateGuestUserAsync() and CreateAnonymousGuestUserAsync() methods
  • Breaking AsyncCountdownEvent object
  • Breaking AsyncManualResetEvent object
  • Bubbles service:
    • Breaking IsGuest() methods
  • Contact object:
    • Breaking Guest property
  • Breaking GuestCreated object

[3.5.0] - 2025-09-01

Info

  • New Sms service permits to send SMS. Specific rights must be defined to use this new service.
  • Add resilience at HTTP request level:
    • If necessary up to 4 more attempts are automatically made by the SDK (after 200, 400, 800 and 1600 ms or using RetryAfter header value returned by the server).
    • It's possible to define your own logic (for tests, depending on the domain used, etc.) by defining your own Http.DelegatingHandler - see HttpRetryMessageHandler object for more details.
  • It's now possible to join several conferences in same time using the same account - need to set JoinMultipleConferences to true in Restrictions object

Fixed

  • Application service:
    • Avoid crash if xmpp or auto-reconnection object has been been already closed / disposed.
  • Bubbles service:
    • Request information from server about an unknown Bubble when a message about user management is received (can occurred when guests are used).
    • Avoid crash when guests are used.
    • Avoid to request too often conference snapshot.
    • BubbleLink can be public (owner and moderators can acces to it) when created by the bubble's owner or private when created by a moderator (only visible to him).
  • Conversations service:
    • Check Peer's Id validity before to request server to create a conversation.
    • When adding a Conversation to the cache, ensure to know the associated Peer (as Contact or Bubble).
  • InstantMessaging service:
    • Use cache first to get a Conversation instead to always create it.
  • MediaPublication object:
    • Ensure to set empty string for MediaId, MediaName, MediaDescription, PeerResource instead of null.

Added

  • Log Http Headers set specifically using the SDK
  • Administration service:
    • UpdateApplicationAsync() method
  • Application service:
    • GetIniFullPath() method
  • Bubbles service:
    • GetBubbleLinkAsync(): optional parameter asPublic (true by default) to get public (created by the owner) or private (created by a moderator) Bubble Link
  • HttpClient object:
    • SetDelegatingHandler(), DefaultDelegatingHandler() methods
  • HttpRetryMessageHandler object:
    • used as default Http.DelegatingHandler by the HttpClient
  • Peer object:
    • CanBeUsedInConversation(), HasValidId(), HasValidJid(), HasValidIdentifier() static methods
    • IsContact(), IsContactWithId(), IsContactWithJid() static methods
    • IsBubble(), IsBubbleWithId(), IsBubbleWithJid(), FromBubbleId(), FromBubbleJid static methods
    • Implicit operator to get Peer from ConferenceTalkerParticipant
  • Restrictions object:
    • JoinMultipleConferences property (false by default)
  • SdkInternalErrorEnum enum:
    • GENERIC_ERROR entry
  • Sms service
    • SendSmsAsync(), SendSmsAndWaitSentConfirmationStatusAsync(), GetSmsProvidersAsync methods
    • SmsProvider object

Changed

  • LogRequest object - used in CustomerCare service:
    • Breaking DeviceDetails field is now a LogRequestData object
    • Breaking Data field has been removed

[3.4.0] - 2025-07-07

Info

  • HubTelephony service is no more in alpha version:
    • Track ongoing calls
    • Voicemail information
    • Device status
    • 3PCC (Third Party Call Control)
  • New CustomerCare service (for user and admin account) permits
    • As admin
      • to ask user using a specific device to provide its logs
      • to get available log request by user and close them eventually
    • As user
      • to store log as feedback on server
      • to acknowledge / reject log request asked by an admin
  • New WebHookEventPipe service (for admin account only) permits to get all events (according subscription event type used) at a Company level (so for all users in this company):
    • device_state to get the status of all devices in Hub Telephony context only (in service, out of service).
    • presence to get the presence of all users including telephony (Hub or Hybrid), calendar (Office 365 or Google) and Microsoft Teams.
    • callog to get all call logs including telephony (Hub or Hybrid) and WebRTC.

Fixed

  • In very few cases, SdkResult<Boolean> may contain a true value instead of false
  • JSON: fix implicit constructors when parsing null objects
  • Bubbles service:
    • If bubble affiliation (i.e. "join all bubbles" presence message) failed, event ConnectionStateChanged is triggered including ConnectionState object with a fatal reason and a specific SdkError.
    • Use correct Jid for MCU service when sending "join all bubbles" presence message
  • Contacts service:
    • fix bad parsing in GetTeamsPresenceStatesAsync() and GetCalendarStatesAsync() methods
    • Contact object
      • InRoster could store invalid value
      • Its parsing is no longer interrupted if Formatfull is not equal to true. Some properties may therefore be read even if they are not expected.
    • ContactAvatarUpdated event could be not triggered
  • Presence object: when PresenceLevel was equal to unavailable, ToString() and ToLogString() methods provided bad results.

Added

  • Administration service:
    • UpdateCompanyEventWebHookAsync(), UpdateCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(), GetCompanyEventSubscriptionStatusAsync() methods
    • CompanyEventWebHook object: Token property
    • CompanyEventSubscription object: EventType, Domain, SubscribedId properties
    • CompanyEventSubscriptionStatus object
    • GetResourcesFromUserAsync() method
  • Application service:
    • GetWebHookEventPipe() method to access new WebHookEventPipe service
    • Even if no EventMode is used, ask server about contacts in Roster in login progress
  • Bubbles service:
    • Bubble object: IsOwnedByGroup andGroupId properties
  • CallLogs service:
    • CallLogAdded event
    • CallLog object: RemoteContact, RemotePhoneNumber and Media properties
  • Contacts service:
    • GetResources() method
    • Contact object: CompanyNameOfGuest properties
  • Conversations service: when adding a conversation with an unknown contact, a request is then made to the server to know them.
  • CustomerCare service:
    • LogRequestAsked, LogRequestAccepted, LogRequestRejected events
    • AcknowledgeLogRequestAskedAsync(), AskLogRequestForUserAsync(), CompleteLogRequestAskedAsync(), RejectLogRequestAskedAsync(), UploadFileForLogRequestAskedAsync() methods
    • StoreLogRequestFeedbackAsync(), UploadFileForLogRequestFeedbackAsync() methods
    • CloseLogRequestAsync(), GetLogRequestAsync(), GetLogRequestsListAsync() methods
    • LogRequest, LogRequestData, LogRequestHardware, LogRequestInfo, LogRequestListData objects
  • FileTags object:
    • Purpose property
  • HttpClient object:
    • AddHttpHeader(), RemoveHttpHeader() and GetHttpHeaders() methods
  • HubTelephony service:
    • CallUpdated, , SupervisionCallUpdated, VoiceMessageNumberUpdated, GroupVoiceMessageNumberUpdated events
    • PBXAgentInfoUpdated event and GetPBXAgentInformation() method
    • HubCall, HubDeviceState, HubEndPoint, HubGroupInfo , HubLeg, HubPartyInfo, HubSupervisionCall, HubVoiceMessage, HubVoiceMessageNumber objects
    • GetCallLineIdentificationRestrictionAsync(), SetCallLineIdentificationRestrictionAsync(), GetCallLineIdentificationsAsync(), SetCurrentCallLineIdentificationsAsync() methods and CallLineIdentificationRestrictionUpdated event
    • VoiceMailAvailable(), GetVoiceMailPhoneNumber(), GetNumberOfVoiceMessages(), GetVoiceMessagesListAsync(), DeleteVoiceMessageAsync(), DeleteAllVoiceMessagesAsync(), MarkVoiceMessageAsReadAsync() methods
    • GetEmergencyNumbersAndOptionsAsync() method
  • PhoneNumber object: IsCloudPbxDefault, IsCloudPbxDDI and ExternalTrunkId properties
  • Util object:
    • StripNS(), ToXmlElement() and ToXElement() to facilitate XML parsing
  • WebHookEventPipe service

Changed

  • For very few specific cases, 429 HTTP Status code is not managed as global connection error
  • Administration service:
    • Breaking CreateUserWithBubbleLinkAsync(): new optional parameters companyNameOfGuest (default value: null)
    • CreateCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(): new optional parameters eventType (default value: presence) and domain (default value: company)
    • CreateCompanyEventWebHookAsync(): new optional parameter token (default value: null)
  • FileStorage service:
    • UploadFileAsync(): new optional parameter options (default value: null)
    • CreateFileDescriptorAsync(): new optional parameter options (default value: null)
  • HybridTelephony service:
    • Breaking HybridPbxAgentInfo object:
      • renamed to PbxAgentInfo
      • IsOXE and IsOXO properties have been replaced by Type which can be set to OXE, OXO or RVCP
  • SdkError object:
    • Breaking CorrelationId and RequesId properties have been removed. Replaced by HttpHeaders

[3.3.0] - 2025-05-13

Info

  • Add support of waiting room / lobby in Bubble
    • Once a bubble link is created, the owner can activate/deactivate a waiting room / lobby
    • Moderators can then accept all or contacts one by one from this waiting room / lobby
  • Rework of search in Contacts service: (by name, tag, email or phone number)
    • New methods permit to get only a list of ContactFound (by name, tag, email or phone number)
    • ContactFound object has new properties to get sub-object if necessary: Contact, DirectoryContact, O365AdContact or Phonebook
    • Personal user directory (if any) is now used if search is done by name or by phone
    • Previous methods are still available but they are now deprecated
    • Examples are available to understand how to use them

Fix

  • Administration service:
    • Bad parsing in GetHubDeviceRegistrationAsync()
    • removes use of body in GetJoinCompanyLinksAsync(), GetHubCloudPBXAsync(), GetHubDevicesAsync()
  • Bubble object: PeerOwner.Type was badly set to EntityType.Bubble instead of EntityType.User
  • Bubbles service:
    • Update BubbleMember.DisplayName for each BubbleMember in all Bubbles when event Comparers.ContactComparerUpdated is triggere d
    • Event BubbleMemberUpdated was not triggered when bubble's owner has changed
  • Contact object: isTv property was not stored when contacts are retrieved with formatFull not set to true

Added

  • Bubble object: HasLobby and AutoRegister properties
  • BubbleJoinedByPublicUrl object: IsWaitingInTheLobby property
  • Bubbles service:
    • ActivateLobbyAsync(), GetContactsInLobbyAsync(), AcceptUsersInLobbyAsync(), DenyUsersInLobbyAsync(), GetBubblesLobbyListAsync(), CancelBubbleAccessRequestAsync() methods and BubbleLobbyUpdated event
    • AutoRegisterUsingBubbleLinkAsync() method
    • GetTvsAsContact() and GetTvs() methods
  • Comparers service: ConversationComparer property which uses by default ConversationComparerByDate
  • Consts.UserSetting object: to store common user settings name
  • ContactFound object: Type, SubType and Value properties. Useful only when new search methods are used
  • Contacts service:
    • Manage all user settings available (not just only 5 hardcoded)
    • GetUserSetting() method (to get user setting by Object). GetUserSettingBooleanValue() and GetUserSettingStringValue() methods are still available e
    • SearchByDisplayNameAsync(), SearchByEmailsAsync(), SearchByPhoneNumberAsync() and SearchByTagAsync() methods
  • Conversation object: LastMessagePeerJid property
  • Conversations service: Take into account server event related to message bookmarks
  • InstantMessaging service: BookmarkMessageAsync() and RemoveBookmarkAsync() methods
  • SearchContactsResults object: PersonalDirectoryContactsList property

Changed

  • Contacts service: deprecated methods SearchContactsByDisplayNameAsync(), SearchContactsByEmailsAsync(), SearchContactsByPhoneNumberAsync() and SearchContactsByTagAsync()
  • Conversations service: GetAllConversationsAsync() and GetAllConversations methods now use Comparers.ConversationComparer to sort result

[3.2.0] - 2025-04-23

Fix

  • Contacts service: Bad display name set when using SearchContactsByDisplayNameAsync(), SearchContactsByTagAsync(), SearchContactsByPhoneNumberAsync() or SearchContactsByEmailsAsync() methods
  • HttpClient: Bad test when an empty request content type is used
  • HybridTelephony service: on internal event established ensure to set CallType.Phone and set only one participant
  • HybridTelephony service: on internal event transferCall ensure to set CallStatus.UNKNOWN for held call (if any)
  • HybridTelephony service: when asking call in progress, CallStatus.PUT_ON_HOLD is set instead of CallStatus.HOLD and the opposite.

Added

  • In S2S or in XMPP event mode, use only one request/stanza to join all bubbles (in connection or reconnection context)
  • Application service: GetCapability() method
  • Const.Capability object: ComputerMode, OtherPhoneMode, SoftPhoneMode, ExternalStorage, RainbowStorage and MainStorage properties
  • Contacts service: UpdateDisplayName() method
  • PhoneNumber object: IsNomadic, IsVoipNomadic, CcdMode, CcdRole and UserType properties (for Hybrid Telephony context only)
  • HybridNomadicStatus object: OtherPhoneModeDenied property
  • HybridPbxAgentInfo object: PbxId property
  • HybridTelephony service: AlternateCallAsync(), HybridNomadicOnOfficePhoneAvailable(), HybridNomadicOnOtherPhoneAvailable(), IsCCDAgent() methods

Changed

  • Breaking Application service:
    • renamed GetHostName() to HostName property
    • removed GetUserLogin() and GetUserPassword(). Use instead UserCredentials property
  • Breaking Contacts service: SetPresenceLevelAsync(), SetBusyPresenceAccordingMediasAsync() and RollbackPresenceSavedAsync() methods now return SdkResult<Presence> instead of SdkResult<Boolean>
  • Breaking HybridTelephony service: GetHybridTelephonyStatus(), DeflectCallAvailable(), TransferCallAvailable() and ConferenceCallAvailable() methods now return Boolean? instead of Boolean
  • Breaking HybridTelephony service: HybridTelephonyStatusUpdated() events now use Boolean? instead of Boolean

[3.1.0] - 2025-03-27

Fix

  • ApplicationToken: In SSO context, its parsing is failing.
  • Conferences service: Internally, the list of MediaPublication could be incorrectly managed which prevents the audio stream subscription from the conference.
  • JSON: fix implicit conversion from JsonNode to Dictionary when a value is null, fix JSONNode to JSON when an object (included itself in a object) has only one key with a null value and avoiNull is set to true.

Added

  • Administration service: DeleteApiKeyAsync() and GetApiKeysAsync() methods
  • Application service: IsSSOAvailableAsync(), GetOAuthAuthorizationEndPoint(), GetOAuthAccessTokenEndPoint(), GetOAuthAuthorizationUrl(), LoginWithOauthAuthorizationCodeAsync() and LoginWithOauthAuthorizationCodeWithoutEventPipeAsync() methods
  • Application service: DeleteApiKeyAsync(), CreateApiKeyAsync(), UpdateApiKeyAsync(), GetApiKeyAsync() and GetApiKeysAsync() methods
  • ApplicationToken object: OAuth, RefreshToken and RedirectUri properties
  • HttpRequestDescriptor object: FormUrlEncodedRequest() method
  • UserCredentials object

Changed

  • Breaking Application service: renamed GetHostName() to HostName property
  • Breaking Application service: removed GetUserLogin() and GetUserPassword(). Use instead UserCredentials property
  • Breaking Contacts service: SetPresenceLevelAsync(), SetBusyPresenceAccordingMediasAsync() and RollbackPresenceSavedAsync() methods now return SdkResult<Presence> instead of SdkResult<Boolean>

[3.0.0] - 2025-03-17

Info

  • Major rework of JSON parser to facilitate its use. All common language runtime types are supported (implicit operators are used)
  • Documentation enhancement: each services (Application, AutoReconnection, Bubbles, Contacts ...) documentation are now splitted by category

Fix

  • Use now UTF8 encoding when creating security token or MD5: allow to support more caracters in password.
  • Avoid crash when dealing with internal list of data (Bubbles, Contacts, ...) which could by modifed in the same time
  • Take into account VCard updates of Guest user
  • Application service: in LoginUsingPreviousCredentialsAsync() avoid to remove from INI file UserLogin and UserPassword
  • Bubbles service: fix affiliation deletion / removal
  • Bubbles service: AddMembersAsync() method when using Moderator as privilege
  • Bubbles service: IsGuest() and IsGuestMode()
  • Bubbles service: BubbleMemberUpdated event could be not triggered
  • Contacts service: ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated() event could be not triggered when a device is going automatically to "away"
  • HttpClient object: dissociate totally Main and Secondary Http client
  • SimpleJson: Fix parsing when null objects are used instead of List<T>, Dictionary<String, String> or Dictionary<String, Object>

Added

  • Administration service: GetHubCloudPBXAsync(), GetHubDevicesAsync(), GetHubDeviceAsync() and GetHubDeviceRegistrationAsync()
  • Administration service: GetOrganisationAsync()
  • CreateGuestUserAsync service: Add companyId optional parameter for CreateGuestUserAsync() and CreateAnonymousGuestUserAsync methods.
  • Application service: ApplicationTokenUpdated event
  • ApplicationMessage object (before a Tuple was used instead)
  • Bubbles service: Unknown contacts found in Bubbles are automatically retrieved (by pack of 500) once event Application.ConnectionStateChanged with Consts.ConnectionStatus.Connected value is triggered
  • Bubbles service: UnknownContactsFound event once all Unknown contacts found are retrieved
  • BubbleInvitation object (before a Tuple was used instead)
  • BubbleMember object: PeerInviting property (as Peer object)
  • Conferences service: GetDataChannelPublisherDetails() method, ConferenceMediaPublicationSubscribersUpdated event
  • Contacts service: GetContactsByJidListAsync() and GetContactsByIdListAsync() methods always return a ContactsListData object
  • Contacts: withPresence optional parameter (default: false) has been added to SearchContactsByDisplayNameAsync() and SearchContactsByTagAsync() methods
  • FileStorage service: RemoveAllFileDescriptorsAsync() method
  • HttpRequestDescriptor object: now accept also *, */* or [type]/* as valid content type
  • InstantMessaging service: AnswerToMessageWithAlternativeContentsAsync(), AnswerToMessageAsync(), AnswerToMessageWithFileAsync() and AnswerToMessageWithStreamAsync() with Message object as first parameter to allow to send a new one in the same context than the message received
  • InstantMessaging service: AnswerToApplicationMessageAsync() with ApplicationMessage object as first parameter to allow to send a new one in the same context than the message received
  • InstantMessaging service: All methods allowing to send a IM has a new parameter to set its storage mode (SdkMessageStorageMode.Store by default)
  • MediaPublication object: MediaId, MediaName, MediaDescription and PeerResource properties
  • MediaPublicationSubscriber object
  • SimpleJson: add implicit support of Dictionary<String, String>.

Changed

  • Breaking Administration service: CreateSelfRegisteredUserAsync() has been removed to be splitted in two specific methods CreateUserWithCompanyLinkAsync() and CreateUserWithBubbleLinkAsync()
  • Breaking Bubble object: OwnerId property (as String) has been replaced by PeerOwner (as Peer object)
  • Breaking FileStorage service: FileStorageUpdated and VoiceMessageUpdated events now manage list of elements when several are updated in same time.
  • Breaking UtilJson: This utility class has been removed (no more necessary). Use JSON, JSONNode, JSONObject or JSONArray instead
  • Breaking Restrictions: MessageStorageMode has been removed since it's now possible to set it when sendind an IM (default value is still the same: SdkMessageStorageMode.Store)
  • Breaking SearchContactsResult: provides now a list of ContactFound (inherited of Contact) and no more a list Contact
  • Bubbles and Conferences service: use Consts.BubbleMemberPrivilege for BubbleMember.Privilege field and use Consts.ConferenceParticipantPrivilege for ConferenceParticipant.Privilege field
  • Log entries about XMPP incoming messages are now added when they are dequeued (and no more when they are queued) to facilitate debugging.

[3.0.0-sts.4.2] - 2024-12-11

Fix

  • Avoid null object when JSON is created
  • Avoid to call ToStringInternal() with Peer and Call objects which are null
  • Fix log entry about event parameter when a String is used since it's also an IEnumerable<char>

Added

  • ErrorDetails property returned by server is mainly just a String but could also be an Object or an Array. All cases are now managed.

[3.0.0-sts.4.1] - 2024-11-26

Fix

  • UtilJSON service: Fix AsJsonNode() when using a String with null value

[3.0.0-sts.4] - 2024-11-22

Fix

  • Ensure to send one by one message to XMPP server (when XMPP event mode is used)
  • Support by default HTTP Status 204 (No Content)
  • Alerts service: SendAlertFeedbackAsync() used AlertMessage object parameter instead of an Alert object
  • Application service: avoid to set default presence to Offline. Use Online instead
  • AutoReconnection service: badly managed 401 Unauthorized when renewing authentication token
  • Bubbles service: avoid triggering BubbleAffiliationChanged in inappropriate cases
  • CallsLog service: correctly manage events sent by the server several time for the same call log
  • Contacts service: correctly manage Unavailable presence (i.e. when a user logout from a device)
  • Conferences service: don't use it if Restrictions.UseConferences is not set to true
  • Conferences service: avoid triggering ConferenceUpdated, ConferenceParticipanstUpdated and ConferenceMediaPublicationsUpdated in inappropriate cases
  • InstantMessaging service: fix MaM (message archive management)
  • Jingle service: some internal events were triggered in a bad order.

Added

  • Administration service: CreateCompanyEventWebHookAsync(), GetCompanyEventWebHookAsync(), DeleteCompanyEventWebHookAsync()
  • Administration service: CreateCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(), GetCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(), DeleteCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync()
  • HubTelephony service: new service to handle Hub Telephony device - first little step as ALPHA VERSION. Cannot be used in production
  • InstantMessagin service: AckMessage support has been added: AckMessageReceived event, SendAckMessageAsync() and AnswerToAckMessageAsync() methods
  • Restrictions object: LogEventParameters (true by default) to log parameters used in event raised by the SDK
  • Restrictions object: LogEventStackTrace (true by default) to log the stack trace when an event is raised by the SDK
  • S2S service: it's now multi tenant. One callback url (webhook) to manage several users (it's still possible to use a different one by user). Enhance connection process and stop it if there is no answer in the callback URL after 5 seconds.
  • S2S service: Message objects now contains also urgency, subject, reply of, deleted, modified and forwarded data
  • S2S service: User Invitation are now managed and it's possible to know when a contact has been added / removed from roster
  • S2S service: It's now possible to reply, forward, delete or modify a message already sent.
  • UtilJSON service: Support more objects (directly manage IDictionary and IList when necessary)
  • UtilJSON service: AsIntList(), AsDoubleList(), AsFloatList(), AsLongList() methods

Changed

  • Breaking Telephony service: Rename the service to HybridTelephony (events and methods have been renamed to use Hybrid in their names to avoid any confusion with HubTelephony)
  • Breaking UtilJSON service: For simplification rename all methods starting with JsonStringFrom___() to ToJson()
  • Breaking UtilJSON service: For simplification rename all methods starting with AsJsonNodeFrom___() to AsJsonNode()

[3.0.0-sts.3] - 2024-10-01

Info

  • In more than 30 objects add ToString(details) (no data hidden) and ToLogString(details) (critical data hidden) with details parameter which could be DetailsLevel.Small, DetailsLevel.Medium (default) or DetailsLevel.Full

Fix

  • Correctly manage 404 HTTP Status code when downloading Avatars (Contacts, Bubbles, ...)
  • Bubbles service: correclty set owner privilege in Bubble.Users list
  • Bubbles service: avoid to store Bubble where the current user is no more subscribed
  • Channels service: Bad LastAvatarUpdateDate when event ChannelAvatarUpdated is triggered
  • Contacts service: Bad LastAvatarUpdateDate when event ContactAvatarUpdated is triggered
  • Contacts service: Bad aggregated/unified presence when an user is removed from roster/network
  • InstantMessage service: Bad XML parsing
  • Invitations service: Bar URI used in CancelInvitationAsync()
  • Jingle service: Remove from SDP hardcoded RTP Header extension
  • Jingle service: Raise internal events in correct order.

Added

  • Bubbles service: BubbleInvitationAccepted and BubbleInvitationRejected events
  • Bubbles service: GetPendingBubbleInvitations() methods
  • Channels service: GetAllChannelsAsync() to get Subscribed and Invited channels in one call
  • Contact object: FormatFull boolean property to know if the object contains all information or only a part

  • Contacts service: Trigger ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated event with Unavailable PresenceLevel when a Contact is removed from roster

  • Breaking Channels service: Rename GetBubbleByPeer() (badly named !) to GetChannelByPeer()
  • Breaking Contacts service: Rename ContactInfoUpdated event to ContactUpdated
  • Breaking Contacts service: CreatePresence() - apply parameter has been removed

  • Several services use now internally awaitable methods from Sharp.WS.Xmpp package

[3.0.0-sts.2] - 2024-07-17

Info

  • Add notion of stackable and unstackable events - both to avoid to trigger several times same event in short period.
    • stackable event: it's triggered only once with all stacked datas - example ContactsAdded event provides a list of contacts
    • unstackable event: it's triggered only once with the final state - example ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated event provides the last aggregated presence for one contact
    • Nothing has changed about the way to use them. Only implementation in SDK has changed
  • Add List extension to sort easily and efficiently any IList object using any property (use Comparer<T> and IComparable<T> interface)
  • Add comparers to sort Contact, Bot, Bubble, Tv, DirectoryContact, Phonebook, O365AdContact with the possibility to change defaults one
  • Internally avoid any use of Task.Wait(), Task.Result and TastCompletionSource not async
  • Enhance performance to fetch all messages archived in a conversation

Fixed

  • Internaly use XmlElement object instead of String from XML to avoid parsing exception
  • Administration service: Fix UpdateCompanySubscriptionAsync() and CreateSelfRegisteredUserAsync(): bad JSON parsing
  • InstantMessaging service: Fix bad sort when fetching archived messages
  • Conversation service: Avoid crash when a message is null

Added

  • AsyncCountdownEvent object: to provide async CountdownEvent object
  • AsyncHelper object: new static class to easily use synchronously asynchronous method
  • AsyncManualResetEvent object: new class to provide async ManualResetEvent object
  • Bubbles service: GetMembersAsContactsAsync(), GetModeratorsAsContactsAsync() and GetUnknownContactsAsync() metohds
  • CancelableDelay object: StartAfter() now supports also async task
  • Company object: AutoAddToUserNetwork property
  • Comparers object: To store all comparers
  • Contacts service: GetContactsByIdList(), GetContactsByIdListAsync() and GetContactsByJidListAsync() methods
  • Conversation service: GetOrCreateConversationFromPeerSync() method
  • InstantMessaging service: GetMessagesAsync() method
  • InstantMessaging service: Ensure to know all members' bubble when fetching messages archived
  • Message object: Inherits from IComparable<T> interface using Date property for the comparison.
  • Peer object: Implicit operator from BubbleMember and Conference objects
  • Util object: RaiseEvent() with list of objects, RaiseStackableEvent() and RaiseUnstackableEvent() methods
  • Util object: RemoveDiacritics() method
  • UtilJson object: AddNode() now supports List<Dictionary<String, String>> and List<Dictionary<String, Object>>
  • UtilJson object: AsJsonNodeFromListOfDictionaryOfString() and AsJsonNodeFromListOfDictionaryOfObjects() methods

Changed

  • Breaking AutoReconnection service: when service is stopped volontarily (logout / cancel), Cancelled event provide a NoError
  • Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed AddContactAsync() to AddMemberAsync()
  • Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed RemoveContactByIdAsync() to RemoveMemberAsync()
  • Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed UpdateContactPrivilegeAsync() to UpdateMemberPrivilegeAsync()
  • Breaking Bubbles service: GetAllBubblesAsync() and GetAllBubbles() - Add memberStatus and memberPrivilege filter parameters
  • Breaking Bubbles service: GetMembers() method: Add memberStatus and memberPrivilege filter parameters
  • Bubbles service: When possible use Peer object instead of Bubble object as parameter in all methods
  • CancelableDelay object: avoid to throw exception when cancelled
  • Breaking ChannelsListsData object renamed to ChannelsListData (without an extra s - typo error)
  • Breaking Conferences service: ConferenceSharingTransfertStatusUpdated object renamed to ConferenceSharingTransferStatusUpdated (without an extra t - typo error)
  • Breaking Conferences service: SendSharingTransfertStatusAsync object renamed to SendSharingTransferStatusAsync (without an extra t - typo error)
  • Breaking Contacts service: ContactAdded event replaced by ContactsAdded (used as stackable event)
  • Breaking Contacts service: RosterContactAdded event replaced by RosterContactsAdded (used as stackable event)
  • Breaking Contacts service: RosterContactRemovedevent replaced by RosterContactsRemoved (used as stackable event)
  • Contacts service: ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated is now used as an unstackable event
  • Contacts service: Avoid to trigger ContactPresenceUpdated and ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated events if not necessary
  • Contacts service: GetAllContacts() accepts two option parameters: inRoster and notInRoster

[3.0.0-sts.1] - 2024-07-01

Info

  • Contains nearly all features of v2.X
  • New features will only been added in V3.X
  • Simplification is the goal of this new release:
    • Use Async/Await pattern
    • No more needs to wait InitializationPerformed. Waiting the end of the login is enough.
    • Peer object is used centrally to describe a Bot, Bubble, CallParticipant, Channel, ConferenceParticipant, Contact, Conversation, MediaService (WebRTC context), DynamicFeed (WebRTC context) or a user known only by a phone number.
    • Implicit operator permits to create Peer object from Bot, Bubble, CallParticipant, Channel, ConferenceParticipant, Contact, Conversation
    • Avoid usage of id/jid in methods and used objects instead
  • Samples will be updated in consequence

Removed

  • AckMessage features in InstantMessaging service. Use instead ApplicationMessage - more versatile and simple
  • AdHocCommand features in InstantMessaging service. Use instead ApplicationMessage - more versatile and simple
  • InitializationPerformed event from Application service. ConnectionStateChanged event is enough.

Added

  • Restrictions object: AcceptBubbleInvitation (False by default). If set to True, automatically accept pending bubble invitation.
  • Restrictions object: AcceptUserInvitation (False by default). If set to True, automatically accept pending user invitation.

[3.0.0-sts.4.1] - 2024-11-26 Fix UtilJSON service: Fix AsJsonNode() when using a String with null value [3.0.0-sts.4] - 2024-11-22 Fix Ensure to send one by one message to XMPP server (when XMPP event mode is used) Support by default HTTP Status 204 (No Content) Alerts service: SendAlertFeedbackAsync() used AlertMessage object parameter instead of an Alert object Application service: avoid to set default presence to Offline. Use Online instead AutoReconnection service: badly managed 401 Unauthorized when renewing authentication token Bubbles service: avoid triggering BubbleAffiliationChanged in inappropriate cases CallsLog service: correctly manage events sent by the server several time for the same call log Contacts service: correctly manage Unavailable presence (i.e. when a user logout from a device) Conferences service: don't use it if Restrictions.UseConferences is not set to true Conferences service: avoid triggering ConferenceUpdated, ConferenceParticipanstUpdated and ConferenceMediaPublicationsUpdated in inappropriate cases InstantMessaging service: fix MaM (message archive management) Jingle service: some internal events were triggered in a bad order. Added Administration service: CreateCompanyEventWebHookAsync(), GetCompanyEventWebHookAsync(), DeleteCompanyEventWebHookAsync() Administration service: CreateCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(), GetCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync(), DeleteCompanyEventSubscriptionAsync() HubTelephony service: new service to handle Hub Telephony device - first little step as ALPHA VERSION. Cannot be used in production InstantMessagin service: AckMessage support has been added: AckMessageReceived event, SendAckMessageAsync() and AnswerToAckMessageAsync() methods Restrictions object: LogEventParameters (true by default) to log parameters used in event raised by the SDK Restrictions object: LogEventStackTrace (true by default) to log the stack trace when an event is raised by the SDK S2S service: it's now multi tenant. One callback url (webhook) to manage several users (it's still possible to use a different one by user). Enhance connection process and stop it if there is no answer in the callback URL after 5 seconds. S2S service: Message objects now contains also urgency, subject, reply of, deleted, modified and forwarded data S2S service: User Invitation are now managed and it's possible to know when a contact has been added / removed from roster S2S service: It's now possible to reply, forward, delete or modify a message already sent. UtilJSON service: Support more objects (directly manage IDictionary and IList when necessary) UtilJSON service: AsIntList(), AsDoubleList(), AsFloatList(), AsLongList() methods Changed Breaking Telephony service: Rename the service to HybridTelephony (events and methods have been renamed to use Hybrid in their names to avoid any confusion with HubTelephony) Breaking UtilJSON service: For simplification rename all methods starting with JsonStringFrom___() to ToJson() Breaking UtilJSON service: For simplification rename all methods starting with AsJsonNodeFrom___() to AsJsonNode() [3.0.0-sts.3] - 2024-10-01 Info In more than 30 objects add ToString(details) (no data hidden) and ToLogString(details) (critical data hidden) with details parameter which could be DetailsLevel.Small, DetailsLevel.Medium (default) or DetailsLevel.Full Fix Correctly manage 404 HTTP Status code when downloading Avatars (Contacts, Bubbles, ...) Bubbles service: correclty set owner privilege in Bubble.Users list Bubbles service: avoid to store Bubble where the current user is no more subscribed Channels service: Bad LastAvatarUpdateDate when event ChannelAvatarUpdated is triggered Contacts service: Bad LastAvatarUpdateDate when event ContactAvatarUpdated is triggered Contacts service: Bad aggregated/unified presence when an user is removed from roster/network InstantMessage service: Bad XML parsing Invitations service: Bar URI used in CancelInvitationAsync() Jingle service: Remove from SDP hardcoded RTP Header extension Jingle service: Raise internal events in correct order. Added Bubbles service: BubbleInvitationAccepted and BubbleInvitationRejected events Bubbles service: GetPendingBubbleInvitations() methods Channels service: GetAllChannelsAsync() to get Subscribed and Invited channels in one call Contact object: FormatFull boolean property to know if the object contains all information or only a part Contact object: LastLoginDate, LoggedSince and LastSeenDate properties Conferences service: new optionnal parameter mediasList in JoinConferenceAsync() Conferences service: AddAudioAsync() Contacts service: UpdateCustomDataAsync(), DeleteCustomDataAsync(), GetUnknownContactIdList() and GetUnknownContactJidList() methods Contacts service: Trigger ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated event with Unavailable PresenceLevel when a Contact is removed from roster Favorites service: DeleteFavoriterAsync() using a Peer object. Invitations service: GetReceivedInvitations(), GetReceivedInvitation(peer), GetSentInvitations() and GetSentInvitation(peer) methods PhoneNumber object: IsMonitored property PresenceLevel object: Unavailable property Changed Breaking Channels service: Rename GetBubbleByPeer() (badly named !) to GetChannelByPeer() Breaking Contacts service: Rename ContactInfoUpdated event to ContactUpdated Breaking Contacts service: CreatePresence() - apply parameter has been removed Breaking Groups service: GetAllMemberAsync() now returns List<Peer> instead of List<String> (User ID list) Breaking Group object: Users is now a List<Peer> instead of List<String> (User ID list) Several services use now internally awaitable methods from Sharp.WS.Xmpp package [3.0.0-sts.2] - 2024-07-17 Info Add notion of stackable and unstackable events - both to avoid to trigger several times same event in short period. stackable event: it's triggered only once with all stacked datas - example ContactsAdded event provides a list of contacts unstackable event: it's triggered only once with the final state - example ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated event provides the last aggregated presence for one contact Nothing has changed about the way to use them. Only implementation in SDK has changed Add List extension to sort easily and efficiently any IList object using any property (use Comparer<T> and IComparable<T> interface) Add comparers to sort Contact, Bot, Bubble, Tv, DirectoryContact, Phonebook, O365AdContact with the possibility to change defaults one Internally avoid any use of Task.Wait(), Task.Result and TastCompletionSource not async Enhance performance to fetch all messages archived in a conversation Fixed Internaly use XmlElement object instead of String from XML to avoid parsing exception Administration service: Fix UpdateCompanySubscriptionAsync() and CreateSelfRegisteredUserAsync(): bad JSON parsing InstantMessaging service: Fix bad sort when fetching archived messages Conversation service: Avoid crash when a message is null Added AsyncCountdownEvent object: to provide async CountdownEvent object AsyncHelper object: new static class to easily use synchronously asynchronous method AsyncManualResetEvent object: new class to provide async ManualResetEvent object Bubbles service: GetMembersAsContactsAsync(), GetModeratorsAsContactsAsync() and GetUnknownContactsAsync() metohds CancelableDelay object: StartAfter() now supports also async task Company object: AutoAddToUserNetwork property Comparers object: To store all comparers Contacts service: GetContactsByIdList(), GetContactsByIdListAsync() and GetContactsByJidListAsync() methods Conversation service: GetOrCreateConversationFromPeerSync() method InstantMessaging service: GetMessagesAsync() method InstantMessaging service: Ensure to know all members' bubble when fetching messages archived Message object: Inherits from IComparable<T> interface using Date property for the comparison. Peer object: Implicit operator from BubbleMember and Conference objects Util object: RaiseEvent() with list of objects, RaiseStackableEvent() and RaiseUnstackableEvent() methods Util object: RemoveDiacritics() method UtilJson object: AddNode() now supports List<Dictionary<String, String>> and List<Dictionary<String, Object>> UtilJson object: AsJsonNodeFromListOfDictionaryOfString() and AsJsonNodeFromListOfDictionaryOfObjects() methods Changed Breaking AutoReconnection service: when service is stopped volontarily (logout / cancel), Cancelled event provide a NoError Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed AddContactAsync() to AddMemberAsync() Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed RemoveContactByIdAsync() to RemoveMemberAsync() Breaking Bubbles service: Renamed UpdateContactPrivilegeAsync() to UpdateMemberPrivilegeAsync() Breaking Bubbles service: GetAllBubblesAsync() and GetAllBubbles() - Add memberStatus and memberPrivilege filter parameters Breaking Bubbles service: GetMembers() method: Add memberStatus and memberPrivilege filter parameters Bubbles service: When possible use Peer object instead of Bubble object as parameter in all methods CancelableDelay object: avoid to throw exception when cancelled Breaking ChannelsListsData object renamed to ChannelsListData (without an extra s - typo error) Breaking Contacts service: ContactAdded event replaced by ContactsAdded (used as stackable event) Breaking Contacts service: RosterContactAdded event replaced by RosterContactsAdded (used as stackable event) Breaking Contacts service: RosterContactRemovedevent replaced by RosterContactsRemoved (used as stackable event) Contacts service: ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated is now used as an unstackable event Contacts service: Avoid to trigger ContactPresenceUpdated and ContactAggregatedPresenceUpdated events if not necessary Contacts service: GetAllContacts() accepts two option parameters: inRoster and notInRoster [3.0.0-sts.1] - 2024-07-01 Info Contains nearly all features of v2.X New features will only been added in V3.X Simplification is the goal of this new release: Use Async/Await pattern No more needs to wait InitializationPerformed. Waiting the end of the login is enough. Peer object is used centrally to describe a Bot, Bubble, CallParticipant, Channel, ConferenceParticipant, Contact, Conversation, MediaService (WebRTC context), DynamicFeed (WebRTC context) or a user known only by a phone number. Implicit operator permits to create Peer object from Bot, Bubble, CallParticipant, Channel, ConferenceParticipant, Contact, Conversation Avoid usage of id/jid in methods and used objects instead Samples will be updated in consequence Removed AckMessage features in InstantMessaging service. Use instead ApplicationMessage - more versatile and simple AdHocCommand features in InstantMessaging service. Use instead ApplicationMessage - more versatile and simple InitializationPerformed event from Application service. ConnectionStateChanged event is enough. Added Restrictions object: AcceptBubbleInvitation (False by default). If set to True, automatically accept pending bubble invitation. Restrictions object: AcceptUserInvitation (False by default). If set to True, automatically accept pending user invitation.
